summary: In this blog post, I share the key lessons I learned building voice-first AI apps, where voice is the main way users interact. From the importance of documentation and API-first design to the necessity of transcripts and centralized voice operations, I cover what works, what doesn't, and how to debug the invisible. The magic of voice-controlled UIs is real, but so are the engineering challenges. Curious about the pitfalls and breakthroughs of building with voice as the primary interface? Read on to find out more.
